LC6Cmax7 Meder - direct
1 corresponded it with the correct evidence item in the 1B number, as well as confirming the name of the CD.
2 Q. And when we say the name of the CD, is that a label that was physically affixed to the CD?
3 A. Yes, it was written on the disc.
4 Q. Will this exhibit assist you in your testimony here today?
5 A. Yes.
6 MS. COMEY: Your Honor, I would ask permission for the witness to refer to this exhibit as an aid during her testimony.
7 MS. MENNINGER: Your Honor, no objection to that, although there is certainly hearsay contained in the far right column, so I assume that won't be part of the testimony.
8 MS. COMEY: Your Honor, I think we can take each objection as it comes.
9 THE COURT: You're not moving for the admission?
10 MS. COMEY: That's correct, your Honor.
11 THE COURT: For now, we'll allow it to be an aid for memory and mindful of potential objections.
12 MS. COMEY: Thank you, your Honor.
13 Ms. Drescher, would you please pull up what's been marked for identification as Government Exhibit 304.
14 BY MS. COMEY:
15 Q. Do you recognize this?
16 A. Yes.
17 SOUTHERN DISTRICT REPORTERS, P.C. (212) 805-0300
18 DOJ-OGR-00012993
